            <fr:title text="Type Universes">Type Universes</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>
  In an abstract sense type universes can be regarded similarly in motivation to <fr:link href="/notes/002q/" title="Grothendieck universe" uri="https://kaierikniermann.github.io/notes/002q/" display-uri="002q" type="local">Grothendieck universes</fr:link> in that they represent a collection (type in this case) of types which are <fr:link href="/notes/002e/" title="Closed set" uri="https://kaierikniermann.github.io/notes/002e/" display-uri="002e" type="local">closed</fr:link> under certain type constructions. There are typically two presentations of type universes either a la Russell or Tarksi, starting with the former we have:
</html:p>
  
    
